'''Bleah''' is an interjection, in use in at least standard [[North American English]].  The quality of the [[emotion]] expressed is more negative than that of '[[Blah]]' and has a slight feeling of [[disgust]]  verging on [[nausea]] included, hence the [[onomatopoeia]] of the '[[Bleah]]' sound.

[[Berkeley Breathed]] may have used 'Bleah' in his "[[Bloom County]]" [[comic strip]] (ca. 1983--1989).

== Examples ==

*"You bought that green [[Station_wagon|station wagon]]?  ''Bleah!''"

